author: Inside Edition
description: Joe Hunter, a contestant from TV's "Survivor" is on a mission to bring justice to the man he believes killed his sister. Hunter, a Sacramento fire captain, is pointing fingers at the man he believes took her life. His name is Mark Lewis, a former pastor who was married to Hunter's sister, Joanna. Lewis has not been charged in connection with Joanna’s death and authorities have ruled her death a suicide. Natalie Morales investigated the case for "48 Hours" and spoke to Inside Edition.
title: 'Survivor's' Joe Hunter Says He Wants Justice For His Sister

author: Inside Edition
description: Two men arrived at a home to buy a laptop that the homeowner listed on Facebook Marketplace. As homeowner Jason Nguyen waited for the $2,700 transaction to go through, he was hit with bear spray. Nguyen grabbed his attacker and a struggle ensued. One of the robbers ran into the house before Nguyen and his wife teamed up to tackle the intruder. Nguyen spoke to Inside Edition's Les Trent. The robbers dropped the spray during their getaway and it is being used as evidence to track them down.
title: Man Attacked With Bear Spray In Attempted Facebook Marketplace Robbery

author: Inside Edition
description: Police raced to a home and urgently tried to get to the roof where they found an elderly man hanging on for dear life. The man slipped while cleaning his clogged gutters of leaves and other debris. Two officers grabbed his arms and pulled him to safety. Officers Jason Sikoski and Caleb Girard spoke with Inside Edition. Inside Edition met up with the team for Gutter Guys. They gave some tips for homeowners looking to clean their gutters themselves.
title: Officers Rescue Elderly Man Hanging On For Dear Life From Roof

author: Inside Edition
description: This holiday season, finding giant Christmas decorations is turning into a mammoth task. Big inflatables, like giant Santas, snowmen and grinches, are in short supply this year, and when you do find them, brace yourself. American businesses have paid $400 million in tariffs this year on Christmas decorations, compared with $26 million in 2024. Dante Holmes and Cynthia Hamilton usually go wild with their Christmas decorations, and they say they could not find large decorations this year.
title: Large Inflatable Christmas Decorations In Short Supply This Year

author: Inside Edition
description: Embattled University of Michigan head coach Sherrone Moore made his first court appearance Friday. During the hearing, the prosecutor detailed an account of Moore allegedly breaking into the home of his executive assistant Paige Schriver, and threatening to kill himself. Moore has been charged with home invasion, stalking and breaking and entering. His bond was set at $25,000 and he will be required to wear GPS monitoring. He was also ordered not to have any contact with Schriver.
title: Former Michigan Football Coach Makes First Court Appearance

author: Inside Edition
description: An emotional Taylor Swift opened up about the foiled terror plot to bomb her concert in Vienna last year. Swift talked about the drama with fellow pop singer Ed Sheeran. Swift broke down in tears after meeting with the families of the three little girls who were stabbed to death in England during a Taylor Swift-themed dance class. The docu-series "Taylor Swift: The End of an Era," gives an intimate look at how Swift pulled off the highest-grossing tour of all time.
title: Taylor Swift Opens Up About Foiled Bomb Attempt At Her Concert

author: Inside Edition
description: Severe flooding in Iraq caused the wall of a boarding school to collapse, but no students were injured thanks to this man. Kemal Fetah Tevekeli tells Turkish media that he saw students fleeing the property by quickly walking along the outside wall. Fearing the worst, he helped usher them away from the structure just moments before the wall collapsed. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 30 Students Saved From Being Crushed By Collapsed Wall

author: Inside Edition
description: In tearful testimony, Alissa Kirby said she and her close friend, Ana, had a heart-to-heart about the stresses in Ana's marriage three days before she was last seen alive.
title: Ana Walshe Friend Testifies At Brian Walshe Trial #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Jerry O'Donnell is a cadet in training at the Asheville Police Academy in North Carolina. The 65-year-old is no stranger to carrying a badge. Back in the day, he played a police officer in the classic police drama "NYPD Blue." O'Donell tells Inside Edition he signed up to be part of the academy to see if they would take him, and they did. O'Donell will graduate from the police academy on January 30th and will be sworn in as an officer in March.
title: Is He The Oldest Rookie Cop In America?

author: Inside Edition
description: The University of Michigan's football coach Sherrone Moore has been fired from his $30 million job, accused of cheating on his wife, and was being held in mental health protective custody.
title: Accusations Emerge About Michigan Coach Sherrone Moore #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Taylor Swift got a standing ovation when she appeared on "The Late Show with Stephen Colbert" in a sculptural dress by designer David Koma.
title: Taylor Swift Stuns On Late Show With Stephen Colbert #shorts

description: Charlie Kirk's alleged assassin made his first in-person court appearance. Tyler Robinson sat between his attorneys, smiling and chatting with them as he awaited the judge.
title: Tyler Robinson Appears In Court #shorts
